<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n10075d"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n10" href="#n10075d">N10 (VI.B.16)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n10all.htm#n10075d"> 75(d)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> under pain of life / league</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">C&apos;est ensuite le roi Louis XI qui, par son ordonnance du 19 juin 1464, &eacute;tablit sur les routes de son royaume, de quatre en quatre <mark>lieues</mark>, &ldquo;des maistres tenant des chevaulx courants pour le service du roy&rdquo;. Ces maistres, ainsi que les chevaucheurs royaux, ne pouvaient, <mark>sous peine de la vie</mark>, s&apos;employer &agrave; d&apos;autres services que celui du roi. <font color="green">[Afterwards, King Louis XI, with his decree of June 19, 1464, established every four leagues on the roads of his kingdom &ldquo;master-riders holding horses at the ready for the service of the king&rdquo;. These knights, as well as the royal riders could not, at the pain of their lives, work in anyone&apos;s service except the king&apos;s]</font> <small> Arthur de Rothschild, <a name="ARHD" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#ARHD"><cite title="source">Histoire de la poste</cite></a> (1876) 3</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
